1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:04,963
<i>Mr. Roja, is it true that you know</i>
<i>where your wife is hiding?</i>

2
00:00:05,046 --> 00:00:06,506
<i>I really don't know where my wife is.</i>

3
00:00:06,589 --> 00:00:07,507
<i>Liar!</i>

4
00:00:07,590 --> 00:00:09,175
<i>Put the Rojas behind bars!</i>

5
00:00:09,259 --> 00:00:10,844
<i>Please stop!</i>

6
00:00:10,927 --> 00:00:12,971
<i>You're wrong about them.</i>

7
00:00:13,054 --> 00:00:16,349
[MIKE] <i>Our family wouldn't still be</i>
<i>alive and together if not for the Rojas.</i>

8
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:19,144
[MINNIE] <i>They risked their lives for us.</i>

9
00:00:19,227 --> 00:00:22,230
<i>I wouldn't be here today</i>
<i>if it weren't for the people</i>

10
00:00:22,313 --> 00:00:24,524
<i>who saved us from the hostage takers.</i>

11
00:00:24,607 --> 00:00:26,651
<i>Liam Roja was one of them.</i>

12
00:00:26,735 --> 00:00:29,404
<i>I'm also giving a shout-out to you,</i>
<i>Olsen Bonifacio.</i>

13
00:00:29,904 --> 00:00:31,823
<i>Special thanks to you, Olsen.</i>

14
00:00:31,906 --> 00:00:32,991
[OLSEN] <i>I like you.</i>

15
00:00:33,074 --> 00:00:36,786
<i>But I also want you to pursue your dreams.</i>

16
00:00:36,870 --> 00:00:38,705
<i>No matter how long it takes,</i>
<i>I'll wait for you.</i>

17
00:00:39,706 --> 00:00:41,416
[ICE] <i>Then wait.</i>

18
00:00:43,418 --> 00:00:44,878
[WENDY] <i>I'm sorry, son.</i>

19
00:00:44,961 --> 00:00:47,380
<i>For all the times I lied to you.</i>

20
00:00:47,464 --> 00:00:49,549
<i>I just wanted to protect you.</i>

21
00:00:49,632 --> 00:00:52,218
<i>Don't worry, Ma. I understand.</i>

22
00:00:52,302 --> 00:00:56,056
<i>Especially now I know</i>
<i>who my real father is.</i>

23
00:00:56,139 --> 00:00:59,267
<i>We need to get Boss Emil.</i>
<i>We need to get Mila!</i>

24
00:00:59,350 --> 00:01:01,269
<i>We'll get your father back, Leni.</i>

25
00:01:01,352 --> 00:01:04,939
[LUCAS]<i> We will help him get</i>
<i>what he really wants.</i>

26
00:01:05,023 --> 00:01:06,066
<i>Ayen is who he wants.</i>

27
00:01:06,149 --> 00:01:07,734
<i>Because if she really wanted to,</i>

28
00:01:07,817 --> 00:01:09,694
<i>she would have come back to us</i>
<i>a long time ago.</i>

29
00:01:09,778 --> 00:01:11,446
<i>You wouldn't understand.</i>

30
00:01:11,529 --> 00:01:14,574
<i>Fathers will never abandon their children.</i>

31
00:01:14,657 --> 00:01:17,702
<i>Isn't Olsen your son? What did you do?</i>

32
00:01:17,786 --> 00:01:19,079
<i>His mother denied it, remember?</i>

33
00:01:23,708 --> 00:01:25,376
You know, Ma, I've been thinking.

34
00:01:26,628 --> 00:01:27,587
When I

35
00:01:28,755 --> 00:01:32,467
had doubts about who my real father was…

36
00:01:35,011 --> 00:01:37,388
I said to myself, "I hope…"

37
00:01:39,057 --> 00:01:40,892
[VOICE BREAKING]
"I hope it's Sir Magnus."

38
00:01:40,975 --> 00:01:43,269
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

39
00:01:43,978 --> 00:01:45,355
I wish he'd been my father.

40
00:01:46,773 --> 00:01:48,191
Because he's rich?

41
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:50,193
Come on, Ma.

42
00:01:51,736 --> 00:01:53,113
No, it's because…

43
00:01:55,406 --> 00:01:56,950
when I was a kid,

44
00:01:58,701 --> 00:02:00,537
just like Grandpa Ben…

45
00:02:02,872 --> 00:02:04,499
he took care of me.

46
00:02:06,084 --> 00:02:07,961
He treated me as if I were his own.

47
00:02:10,463 --> 00:02:13,049
After all that has happened,

48
00:02:14,425 --> 00:02:17,929
and with what's happening now,
is it still what you wish for?

49
00:02:19,681 --> 00:02:20,807
Ma.

50
00:02:22,308 --> 00:02:24,352
Was he really oblivious

51
00:02:25,270 --> 00:02:27,480
to Greta's actions?

52
00:02:27,564 --> 00:02:33,403
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

53
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:36,322
I think so, yes.

54
00:02:39,367 --> 00:02:41,119
- [SIGHS HEAVILY]
- Because…

55
00:02:41,202 --> 00:02:44,122
He risked his life for us so many times.

56
00:02:44,873 --> 00:02:45,790
Right?

57
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:50,128
There's a lot about his wife
that he doesn't know,

58
00:02:51,462 --> 00:02:54,132
which he only discovered
during the hostage situation.

59
00:02:54,215 --> 00:02:55,592
Right?

60
00:02:58,887 --> 00:03:01,139
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [OLSEN GRUNTS]

61
00:03:01,222 --> 00:03:03,558
[VOICE TREMBLING] <i>G--Grandpa!</i>

62
00:03:04,934 --> 00:03:06,769
<i>Grandpa!</i>

63
00:03:06,853 --> 00:03:08,021
[BEN WHIMPERING]

64
00:03:08,897 --> 00:03:11,941
[SCREAMING] <i>Chief! Chief! Chief!</i>

65
00:03:12,025 --> 00:03:14,444
- [OLSEN WHIMPERING]
- <i>Chief! Chief!</i>

66
00:03:14,527 --> 00:03:16,279
<i>- Chief!</i>
<i>- No, Grandpa! No!</i>

67
00:03:16,362 --> 00:03:17,322
<i>Grandpa Ben!</i>

68
00:03:17,405 --> 00:03:22,577
- [OLSEN SOBBING] <i>Grandpa, why?!</i>
<i>- Pa!</i>

69
00:03:22,660 --> 00:03:23,870
<i>Pa!</i>

70
00:03:23,953 --> 00:03:25,663
[MACKY] <i>Rita, help me!</i>

71
00:03:25,747 --> 00:03:31,878
- [MACKY GROANING, CRYING]
- Macky.

72
00:03:32,503 --> 00:03:35,757
<i>- Pa!</i>
<i>- Why, Grandpa? Why?!</i>

73
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:38,801
- [SOBBING] <i>Pa! Pa!</i>
- [SOBBING]

74
00:03:38,885 --> 00:03:44,098
<i>- Why did you do that?!</i>
<i>- Pa.</i>

75
00:03:44,182 --> 00:03:47,060
<i>- Why?!</i>
<i>- Pa!</i>

76
00:03:47,143 --> 00:03:49,062
<i>- Anyone! Help!</i>
<i>- Grandpa.</i>

77
00:03:50,104 --> 00:03:53,066
What if he knows where Greta is?

78
00:03:54,984 --> 00:03:56,361
Olsen.

79
00:03:57,403 --> 00:04:01,783
Someone needs to be held accountable
for your Grandpa Ben's death.

80
00:04:03,743 --> 00:04:06,287
It's Greta's fault.

81
00:04:13,002 --> 00:04:14,712
I know a place.

82
00:04:17,507 --> 00:04:19,259
It's a property owned by the Rojas.

83
00:04:21,886 --> 00:04:24,013
Ma'am Greta could be hiding there.

84
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:30,895
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

85
00:04:40,863 --> 00:04:47,829
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

86
00:05:20,862 --> 00:05:21,821
[CAR HORN HONKING]

87
00:05:24,032 --> 00:05:29,662
[CAR ENGINE REVVING]

88
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:34,250
[CAR DOORS OPENING]

89
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:37,712
[CAR DOORS CLOSING]

90
00:05:39,088 --> 00:05:40,339
[KEY CLINKS]

91
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:41,841
- Take care of it, all right?
- [BOTH LAUGH]

92
00:05:41,924 --> 00:05:43,384
Of course, man. Thank you.

93
00:05:44,927 --> 00:05:46,012
Olsen?

94
00:05:46,846 --> 00:05:48,890
Wait, where are you going?

95
00:05:51,142 --> 00:05:53,936
I'll tell you about it when I confirm it.

96
00:05:54,020 --> 00:05:55,521
Confirm what?

97
00:05:56,105 --> 00:05:57,607
It could be dangerous.

98
00:05:57,690 --> 00:05:59,108
We'll come with you.

99
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:00,526
Don't.

100
00:06:01,444 --> 00:06:02,904
No need to get dragged into it.

101
00:06:04,489 --> 00:06:06,157
So it is dangerous.

102
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:08,868
Bro, if you need it,

103
00:06:09,827 --> 00:06:11,245
I have bodyguards.

104
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:15,166
It's okay. There's no need for that.

105
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,126
Thanks again.

106
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:20,546
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

107
00:06:20,630 --> 00:06:23,341
Don't worry, I'll return this to you
without a scratch.

108
00:06:26,761 --> 00:06:30,264
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

109
00:06:31,224 --> 00:06:34,852
[CAR ENGINE STARTING]

110
00:06:41,359 --> 00:06:42,610
[CAR HORN HONKING]

111
00:06:44,529 --> 00:06:49,117
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

112
00:06:56,749 --> 00:07:00,336
[MINNIE] Thank you for offering
the services of your hospital,

113
00:07:00,419 --> 00:07:01,754
Doc Jessie, Connie.

114
00:07:01,838 --> 00:07:03,756
No problem, Architect.

115
00:07:04,757 --> 00:07:08,553
Think carefully about what
we discussed earlier.

116
00:07:08,636 --> 00:07:13,015
If you are interested in our approach
for your treatment,

117
00:07:13,099 --> 00:07:14,225
just call us.

118
00:07:15,143 --> 00:07:19,230
We really like the proposal.
We think it could work.

119
00:07:19,313 --> 00:07:21,232
Yeah. That's right.

120
00:07:21,315 --> 00:07:24,277
So, thank you. Thank you so much.

121
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:27,780
Oh, you. Who else will have our backs
if not each other?

122
00:07:27,864 --> 00:07:32,618
After all that has happened to us,
I think we're connected for life.

123
00:07:32,702 --> 00:07:35,621
- We're like a family now.
- [MINNIE] Thank you.

124
00:07:35,705 --> 00:07:38,332
Oh, where's Maddie?

125
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:42,211
Oh, she decided to stay behind at home.

126
00:07:42,295 --> 00:07:46,632
However, she already misses
all of you, especially Liam.

127
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:49,427
The accusations against them
are very serious, huh?

128
00:07:49,510 --> 00:07:50,344
[CLICKS TONGUE]

129
00:07:50,428 --> 00:07:53,514
You know, I can't imagine that
Greta's involved in all that.

130
00:07:53,598 --> 00:07:55,850
- I know, right?
- I know.

131
00:07:55,933 --> 00:07:57,477
I hope they're okay.

132
00:07:57,560 --> 00:08:00,146
Maddie wants to see them too.

133
00:08:00,938 --> 00:08:02,273
Seriously.

134
00:08:03,691 --> 00:08:07,320
[FORLORN MUSIC PLAYING]

135
00:08:10,531 --> 00:08:12,283
You just never listen!

136
00:08:14,035 --> 00:08:15,995
What are you doing back there?!

137
00:08:16,078 --> 00:08:19,123
Rita called me, all worried.

138
00:08:19,207 --> 00:08:21,792
Where are you off to
that you had to borrow the car?

139
00:08:21,876 --> 00:08:22,752
[WHISPERS] Oh boy…

140
00:08:22,835 --> 00:08:25,171
Come on. Where?

141
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:27,465
[WENDY] Where?!

142
00:08:28,257 --> 00:08:29,717
How annoying!

143
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:34,138
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

144
00:08:54,617 --> 00:08:55,535
Get in.

145
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:04,293
So where are you going, Olsen?

146
00:09:04,377 --> 00:09:06,087
[MUTTERS] Oh boy.

147
00:09:09,924 --> 00:09:11,467
You know where, Ma.

148
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:13,678
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

149
00:09:13,761 --> 00:09:17,223
And no, you cannot come.

150
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:19,559
If you know where Greta is,

151
00:09:19,642 --> 00:09:22,103
why don't you just tell the police?

152
00:09:22,687 --> 00:09:25,523
I want to make sure first, Ma.

153
00:09:25,606 --> 00:09:28,401
I don't want anyone else
to get dragged into this.

154
00:09:28,484 --> 00:09:29,944
Okay?

155
00:09:30,027 --> 00:09:31,487
Which is why

156
00:09:32,363 --> 00:09:35,199
I'm bringing you back.

157
00:09:36,492 --> 00:09:38,828
How did you find out about this place?

158
00:09:41,289 --> 00:09:45,793
Son, I know you're
hiding something from me.

159
00:09:46,669 --> 00:09:49,755
Didn't we promise
not to keep secrets anymore?

160
00:09:54,427 --> 00:10:01,309
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

161
00:10:01,392 --> 00:10:02,351
<i>What's wrong?</i>

162
00:10:02,435 --> 00:10:09,150
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

163
00:10:09,233 --> 00:10:10,318
<i>Is something wrong?</i>

164
00:10:14,822 --> 00:10:18,909
<i>I don't like it</i>
<i>when you bring me here, Magnus.</i>

165
00:10:20,494 --> 00:10:22,705
<i>Why? It's a great rest house.</i>

166
00:10:27,043 --> 00:10:30,588
<i>I've actually been wondering why</i>
<i>no one has bought it yet.</i>

167
00:10:31,797 --> 00:10:34,258
<i>It has been on the market for months now.</i>

168
00:10:34,342 --> 00:10:40,306
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

169
00:10:40,389 --> 00:10:46,145
<i>Magnus, it's so isolated here.</i>
<i>So far away from everyone.</i>

170
00:10:46,228 --> 00:10:48,439
<i>Do you know how that makes me feel?</i>

171
00:10:48,522 --> 00:10:53,486
<i>I feel like I'm a dirty secret</i>
<i>you're trying to hide.</i>

172
00:10:54,195 --> 00:10:56,447
<i>Look, come here.</i>

173
00:10:59,158 --> 00:11:01,494
<i>This is only temporary.</i>

174
00:11:02,370 --> 00:11:04,747
<i>You're not a dirty secret.</i>

175
00:11:04,830 --> 00:11:06,374
[AYEN EXHALES HEAVILY]

176
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:10,044
[MUSIC TURNS UNSETTLING]

177
00:11:10,127 --> 00:11:12,129
<i>Come on, don't worry.</i>

178
00:11:12,213 --> 00:11:14,799
<i>I will get you the townhouse</i>
<i>that you want.</i>

179
00:11:16,384 --> 00:11:19,595
<i>For you and our baby.</i>

180
00:11:19,678 --> 00:11:25,684
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

181
00:11:42,827 --> 00:11:43,828
[MAGNUS GRUNTS]

182
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:45,663
<i>Yeah.</i>

183
00:11:56,924 --> 00:11:57,842
<i>Mm…</i>

184
00:12:00,136 --> 00:12:02,638
<i>It's only temporary, you know.</i>

185
00:12:02,721 --> 00:12:06,892
<i>Come on. Let's just enjoy</i>
<i>this beautiful house</i>

186
00:12:06,976 --> 00:12:09,562
<i>in our little corner of the world.</i>

187
00:12:11,105 --> 00:12:13,023
<i>Please, Mademoiselle.</i>

188
00:12:14,859 --> 00:12:16,110
<i>S'il vous plaît?</i>

189
00:12:16,193 --> 00:12:17,361
<i>You're so silly.</i>

190
00:12:18,654 --> 00:12:20,030
<i>The baby, okay?</i>

191
00:12:20,114 --> 00:12:21,198
<i>Hmm?</i>

192
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:29,457
[GRUNTS SOFTLY]

193
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:36,505
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

194
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:41,760
I know it was wrong, Ma.

195
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:46,974
I knew what Sir Magnus
and Ayen were doing wasn't right.

196
00:12:47,808 --> 00:12:49,518
And I let it happen.

197
00:12:50,895 --> 00:12:54,648
That's why Liam was angry at me.

198
00:12:55,399 --> 00:12:58,319
We didn't speak for years, remember?

199
00:12:58,402 --> 00:12:59,695
That's why.

200
00:13:01,906 --> 00:13:03,866
But what could I do?

201
00:13:03,949 --> 00:13:05,701
I just worked for him.

202
00:13:06,827 --> 00:13:08,496
[SIGHS SOFTLY]

203
00:13:10,539 --> 00:13:11,582
That's it.

204
00:13:11,665 --> 00:13:13,292
After…

205
00:13:16,879 --> 00:13:21,550
After Sir Magnus
and Ayen's relationship ended…

206
00:13:24,929 --> 00:13:27,223
I heard him and Ma'am Greta

207
00:13:28,182 --> 00:13:30,559
arguing about the property.

208
00:13:30,643 --> 00:13:35,064
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

209
00:13:35,147 --> 00:13:38,400
<i>Why don't we just sell the rest house?</i>

210
00:13:39,860 --> 00:13:43,572
[MAGNUS] <i>We can't sell</i>
<i>the rest house, Greta.</i>

211
00:13:43,656 --> 00:13:48,202
<i>What if the buyer builds a new structure?</i>

212
00:13:48,285 --> 00:13:50,704
<i>No, no. We can't. We cannot sell it.</i>

213
00:13:52,373 --> 00:13:54,833
<i>This is our secret, okay?</i>

214
00:13:55,918 --> 00:13:57,795
Don't worry, okay?

215
00:13:57,878 --> 00:14:00,172
<i>After all, the property</i>
<i>is not yet in our name.</i>

216
00:14:00,256 --> 00:14:03,175
<i>The documents have not been signed yet.</i>
<i>We can still hide this.</i>

217
00:14:03,259 --> 00:14:09,557
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

218
00:14:17,189 --> 00:14:18,691
What were they hiding?

219
00:14:20,359 --> 00:14:21,986
I don't know, but…

220
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:25,322
I have a feeling Ma'am Greta is there.

221
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:29,326
No one else knows about the property.

222
00:14:30,411 --> 00:14:31,620
Not even Liam.

223
00:14:33,539 --> 00:14:34,832
You can't be sure.

224
00:14:35,791 --> 00:14:41,797
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

225
00:14:46,051 --> 00:14:47,761
[LIAM] The rest house by King's Road.

226
00:14:47,845 --> 00:14:50,014
The one that's so difficult to sell.

227
00:14:51,515 --> 00:14:53,392
You think Mama's there?

228
00:14:53,475 --> 00:14:56,186
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

229
00:14:56,270 --> 00:15:00,149
Well, it's most probable,
since that place is hidden far away.

230
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:02,359
A lot of people don't know about it.

231
00:15:04,069 --> 00:15:05,738
What if she's really there?

232
00:15:06,947 --> 00:15:10,451
We'll have to do our best to convince her
to surrender to the police.

233
00:15:10,534 --> 00:15:13,871
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

234
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:38,729
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

235
00:15:46,403 --> 00:15:52,576
[MONITOR BEEPING]

236
00:16:08,509 --> 00:16:14,974
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

237
00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:28,487
[SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING]

238
00:16:44,753 --> 00:16:51,385
[SINISTER MUSIC CONTINUES]

239
00:16:51,468 --> 00:16:58,017
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

240
00:17:12,489 --> 00:17:13,657
Sir.

241
00:17:13,741 --> 00:17:14,742
Doc.

242
00:17:16,076 --> 00:17:17,453
He's awake.

243
00:17:18,287 --> 00:17:20,289
He is conscious and responsive.

244
00:17:20,372 --> 00:17:24,126
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

245
00:17:24,209 --> 00:17:25,085
[MONITOR BEEPS]

246
00:17:29,965 --> 00:17:36,930
[MONITOR BEEPING]

247
00:17:37,014 --> 00:17:40,225
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

248
00:17:40,309 --> 00:17:41,435
He's awake?

249
00:17:42,936 --> 00:17:44,313
I suspect that…

250
00:17:44,396 --> 00:17:45,856
[POLICEMAN] He's pretending?

251
00:17:49,568 --> 00:17:51,945
He's ready for transfer into your custody.

252
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:57,701
- [PHONE RINGING]
- Sir.

253
00:17:58,410 --> 00:18:00,579
The doctor said he's ready
to be transferred.

254
00:18:01,538 --> 00:18:07,836
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

255
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:09,463
[DOOR SQUEAKS OPEN]

256
00:18:11,006 --> 00:18:12,049
Greta?

257
00:18:12,132 --> 00:18:13,342
Ma!

258
00:18:16,136 --> 00:18:16,970
[LIAM] Ma!

259
00:18:17,554 --> 00:18:18,680
Greta?

260
00:18:22,101 --> 00:18:24,353
We know you're here, Greta.

261
00:18:26,688 --> 00:18:27,981
[DOOR CLOSES]

262
00:18:28,565 --> 00:18:29,775
Ma!

263
00:18:30,359 --> 00:18:35,823
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

264
00:18:37,241 --> 00:18:38,534
[DOOR OPENS]

265
00:18:39,159 --> 00:18:40,285
Ma!

266
00:18:53,465 --> 00:19:00,472
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

267
00:19:09,106 --> 00:19:10,315
[MAGNUS] <i>It all started with me.</i>

268
00:19:10,399 --> 00:19:13,694
<i>But even though it pains me,</i>
<i>you have to surrender to the police.</i>

269
00:19:13,777 --> 00:19:14,611
[LIAM] <i>Ma.</i>

270
00:19:14,695 --> 00:19:17,573
[CRYING] <i>Even if you force me to,</i>
<i>I won't surrender!</i>

271
00:19:17,656 --> 00:19:19,992
[OLSEN] <i>I have a feeling</i>
<i>Ma'am Greta is there.</i>

272
00:19:20,075 --> 00:19:23,120
<i>If you truly love us,</i>
<i>you'll do the right thing.</i>

273
00:19:23,203 --> 00:19:25,080
[WENDY] <i>Just turn yourself in, Greta.</i>

274
00:19:26,081 --> 00:19:29,042
- [GRETA]<i> Wendy.</i>
- [WENDY] <i>That's for my father!</i>

275
00:19:29,126 --> 00:19:32,796
<i>She can't run away from this.</i>
<i>So many people died.</i>

276
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:34,089
<i>Ma?</i>

277
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:35,048
<i>Ma!</i>

278
00:19:35,883 --> 00:19:36,842
<i>Ma!</i>

279
00:19:36,925 --> 00:19:38,427
<i>Ma, open the door!</i>

280
00:19:39,303 --> 00:19:40,345
- [CRYING]
<i>- Ma!</i>

281
00:19:40,429 --> 00:19:43,015
[LIAM BANGING ON DOOR]
<i>Open the door, Ma!</i>

282
00:19:43,098 --> 00:19:44,641
[BANGING ON DOOR]

283
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:50,022
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
